<body>
    <div class="container">
        <header>
            <h1>Cheesy Broccoli Turkey Dog Scramble</h1>
            <p class="intro">A savory and protein-packed breakfast option that brings together turkey hotdogs, cheddar cheese, and broccoli for a quick and satisfying meal.</p>
        </header>

        <section class="recipe-info">
            <div class="recipe-meta">
                <p><strong>Prep Time:</strong> 5 minutes</p>
                <p><strong>Cook Time:</strong> 10 minutes</p>
                <p><strong>Total Time:</strong> 15 minutes</p>
                <p><strong>Servings:</strong> 2</p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="ingredients">
            <h2>Ingredients</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>2 turkey hotdogs, sliced</li>
                <li>1/2 cup cheddar cheese, shredded</li>
                <li>1/2 cup broccoli, chopped</li>
                <li>2 large eggs</li>
                <li>1 tbsp hot sauce (optional)</li>
                <li>Salt and pepper to taste</li>
                <li>1 tbsp oil or butter for cooking</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="instructions">
            <h2>Instructions</h2>
            <ol>
                <li>Heat oil or butter in a pan over medium heat.</li>
                <li>Add the sliced turkey hotdogs and cook for 2-3 minutes until slightly browned.</li>
                <li>Add the chopped broccoli and saut√© for another 2-3 minutes until tender.</li>
                <li>Crack the eggs into the pan and scramble, stirring occasionally.</li>
                <li>Stir in shredded cheddar cheese until melted and evenly distributed.</li>
                <li>Add hot sauce, salt, and pepper to taste, then serve immediately.</li>
            </ol>
        </section>

        <section class="tips">
            <h2>Tips & Variations</h2>
            <p>For added flavor, try sprinkling some paprika or garlic powder into the scramble. You can also substitute the turkey hotdogs with chicken sausage or vegetarian alternatives.</p>
        </section>

        <footer>
            <p>Enjoyed this recipe? Share it with friends or leave a comment below!</p>
        </footer>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
